# Conventional Commits

All commit messages MUST follow this format:

```
<type>(<optional scope>): <short description>

[optional body]

[optional footer — BREAKING CHANGE: <description>]
```

## Allowed Types

| Type       | When to use                                      |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| `feat`     | A new feature                                    |
| `fix`      | A bug fix                                        |
| `chore`    | Maintenance, dependency updates, config changes  |
| `docs`     | Documentation changes only                      |
| `test`     | Adding or fixing tests                           |
| `refactor` | Code change that is neither a fix nor a feature  |
| `perf`     | Performance improvement                          |
| `ci`       | CI/CD pipeline changes                           |
| `build`    | Build system or tooling changes                  |
| `revert`   | Reverts a previous commit                        |

## Breaking Changes

Append `!` after the type, or add `BREAKING CHANGE:` in the footer:

```
feat!: rename RateLimiter constructor options
```

```
feat: add new auth flow

BREAKING CHANGE: `userId` field is now required in RateLimitContext
```

## Examples

```
# Good
feat(adapters): add Koa middleware
fix: handle null IP address in IPv6 normalization
chore: upgrade ioredis to v5.4
docs: update README with cluster config example
test: add unit tests for circuit breaker recovery
refactor(redis): extract script loader into separate class
perf: reduce Redis round-trips using local reservoir
ci: add semantic-release to release workflow
build: add exports field to package.json
revert: revert "feat: experimental SSM hot-reload"

# Bad — will be blocked by commitlint
added koa adapter
Fixed null IP bug
WIP
update stuff
```

## Line Length Rules

commitlint enforces these hard limits — violating them blocks the commit:

| Part              | Max length | Rule                    |
| ----------------- | ---------- | ----------------------- |
| Subject (1st line) | 100 chars  | `header-max-length`     |
| Body lines        | 100 chars  | `body-max-line-length`  |
| Footer lines      | 100 chars  | `footer-max-line-length`|

When writing a multi-line body, wrap at ~80 characters to stay safe:

```
# Good — each body line is under 100 chars
chore: initialize project with essential configurations

Added commitlint for standardized commit messages and a LICENSE file.
Updated package.json with new package name and devDependencies for
semantic-release. Introduced GitHub Actions workflow for releases.

# Bad — single body line exceeds 100 chars
chore: initialize project with essential configurations

Added commitlint configuration for standardized commit messages and a LICENSE file with MIT licensing. Updated package.json to reflect the new package name.
```

## Version Bump Rules (semantic-release)

| Commit type              | Version bump          |
| ------------------------ | --------------------- |
| `fix:`                   | patch (1.0.0 → 1.0.1) |
| `feat:`                  | minor (1.0.0 → 1.1.0) |
| `feat!:` / `BREAKING CHANGE:` | major (1.0.0 → 2.0.0) |
| `chore:`, `docs:`, etc.  | no release            |
